# ModelBound skill authoring

When editing skill files:

- Frontmatter MUST include `name` (kebab-case) and `description` (30–400 chars naming concrete triggers).
- Include `allowed_tools` when the skill performs file edits, shell execution, or network calls. Prefer the smallest set.
- Lead with a `## When to use` section listing concrete situations, not abstract themes.
- Use numbered steps for procedures; avoid prose paragraphs longer than 3 sentences.
- Keep the body under ~2,000 tokens. If it grows past 5,000, split into sub-skills.
- Avoid vague verbs ("consider", "maybe", "could"); prefer imperatives ("run", "check", "report").
- Cite source docs for any factual or policy claim.
- Do not duplicate content that already lives in a Project Rule — link to the rule instead.
- After substantive edits, suggest `/mb-findings <file>` then `/mb-pipeline <file> --stage test_optimize`.
